<h1 class="hero-h">Fractional executive pricing 2026: <em>what you should actually pay.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Fractional executive pricing varies more than buyers realize — and the variance correlates poorly with quality. This is the honest 2026 pricing landscape, based on what real engagements actually cost in B2B mid-market.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">The short version</div><p class="verdict-p">Typical fractional executive monthly retainers in 2026: <strong>CMO $8K-$25K</strong>, <strong>CRO $10K-$25K</strong>, <strong>COO $10K-$25K</strong>, <strong>CFO $8K-$20K</strong>, <strong>Head of Growth $8K-$20K</strong>. All for 1-2 days/week, 12-18 month engagements typical. Pricing varies by stage (lower for $1M-$5M ARR, higher for $20M-$50M), scope, and industry expertise. Compare to full-time hires at $400K-$700K all-in annually.</p></div>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Why pricing varies</h2><p class="body">Three drivers of price variance in fractional executive engagements:<br><br>1. <strong>Stage of company.</strong> $1M-$5M ARR engagements lean lower (less complexity, less budget). $20M-$50M ARR engagements lean higher (more complexity, more budget).<br>2. <strong>Scope.</strong> Strategic advisory at the lower end. Strategy + hands-on execution + team management at the higher end.<br>3. <strong>Industry expertise.</strong> Generic operators charge less. Operators with specific industry depth (SaaS, fintech, healthcare, etc.) charge premium for fit.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional CMO pricing</h2><p class="body">$8K-$25K/month typical. Variance:<br>• Solo founder + early company: $8K-$12K<br>• Growth-stage SaaS with marketing team: $12K-$18K<br>• Mid-market with complex GTM: $18K-$25K<br>Compare to: full-time CMO at $300K-$500K all-in. <a href='/fractional-cmo'>See Treetop's fractional CMO engagement model →</a></p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional CRO pricing</h2><p class="body">$10K-$25K/month typical. Variance:<br>• Companies under $5M ARR rarely need fractional CRO — sales motion still founder-led<br>• $5M-$20M ARR: $10K-$18K<br>• $20M-$50M+ ARR: $18K-$25K<br>Compare to: full-time CRO at $300K-$500K base + variable. <a href='/fractional-cro'>See full guide →</a></p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional COO pricing</h2><p class="body">$10K-$25K/month typical. Variance:<br>• $5M-$15M ARR: $10K-$18K<br>• $15M-$30M ARR: $18K-$25K<br>Compare to: full-time COO at $300K-$500K base + equity. <a href='/fractional-coo'>See full guide →</a></p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional CFO pricing</h2><p class="body">$8K-$20K/month typical. Often slightly lower than other fractional executive roles because the work is more time-defined (close cycles, board prep) vs continuous strategic ownership. Variance:<br>• $3M-$10M ARR: $8K-$14K<br>• $10M-$30M ARR: $14K-$20K<br>Compare to: full-time CFO at $250K-$400K base. <a href='/fractional-cfo'>See full guide →</a></p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Fractional Head of Growth pricing</h2><p class="body">$8K-$20K/month typical. Slightly lower than CMO because narrower scope. Variance:<br>• $1M-$5M ARR: $8K-$12K<br>• $5M-$20M ARR: $12K-$20K<br>Compare to: full-time VP Growth at $300K-$450K all-in. <a href='/fractional-head-of-growth'>See full guide →</a></p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">What you should NOT pay for</h2><p class="body">Three flags that suggest you're being overcharged:<br><br>1. <strong>Hourly billing above $400/hr without specialized expertise.</strong> Most fractional executive work runs $200-$350/hr effective rate.<br>2. <strong>Junior 'fractional' operators charging senior rates.</strong> A real fractional executive has 12+ years CMO/VP-level operating experience. Charge by experience, not title.<br>3. <strong>'Fractional CMO' or similar from agency-style firms that try to staff multiple people on one engagement.</strong> You want one senior operator with continuity, not a rotating cast.<br><br>Quality varies wildly. Reference checks matter more than the resume.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><h2 class="h2">Total fractional executive team cost</h2><p class="body">Companies that build a fractional executive team (CMO + CRO + CFO + COO) typically run $35K-$80K/month combined for 1-2 days/week of each role. Compare to: hiring all four full-time at $400-$700K each = $1.6M-$2.8M annually all-in.<br><br>Fractional is 25-40% of the full-time cost for the same seniority. Trade-off: part-time hours and shorter engagement length. Math usually favors fractional for $5M-$30M ARR companies; full-time wins above $50M ARR for most functions.</p></div></section>

